                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d890">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-11-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 13, 1896.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1187.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: On the 7th instant Moustapha Bey handed to me a
                    translation of a telegraphed memorandum which he had received from the Ottoman
                    foreign office in regard to, first, the inspection of foreign vessels in Turkish
                    ports and the prevention of the landing of persons alleged to be disaffected
                    toward the Ottoman Government, to which end the cooperation of the United States
                    representatives is suggested; and secondly, the prevention of revolutionary
                    publications in the United States and the expulsion of Armenian agitators.</p>
                <p>For your information I inclose a copy both of the memorandum as translated and my
                    reply.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
